2":"1422","1344":"1344","1399":"1399","1365":"1365","1364":"1364","1397":"1397","31 DEC 1397":"31 December 1397","BEF    1397":"before 1397","27 October 1383":"27 October 1383","1418":"1418","Irnham, South Kesteven District, Lincolnshire, England":"Irnham, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom","Irnham, Lincolnshire, England":"Irnham, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Luttrell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): from a diminutive of Old French <i>loutre</i> ‘otter’ (from Latin <i>lutra</i>), applied as a nickname for someone thought to resemble an otter, or a metonymic occupational name for someone who hunted otters (for their pelts). Compare   Luter   and   Litteral  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Luttrull","meanings":["English: variant of   Luttrell  ."]},{"name":"Littrell","meanings":["English: variant of   Luttrell  ."]},{"name":"Littrel","meanings":["English: variant of   Luttrell  ."]},{"name":"Litteral","meanings":["Altered form of English   Luttrell  ."]},{"name":"Luter","meanings":["from Old French <i>loutre</i> ‘otter’, either used as a nickname, or alternatively as a metonymic occupational name to denote an otter hunter.","variant of   Luther   2.","English:"]}]},{"name":"Andrew","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the Greek name <i>Andreas</i>, a short form of any of various compound names derived from <i>andr-</i> ‘man, warrior’. In the New Testament this is the name of the first disciple to be called by Jesus. After the Resurrection,  St Andrew  preached in Asia Minor and Greece. He is traditionally believed to have been crucified at Patras in Achaia. He was one of the most popular saints of the Middle Ages and was adopted as the patron of Scotland, Russia, and Greece. It has long been among the most popular boys' names in the English-speaking world, especially in Scotland. Its popularity in England was further enhanced by its use as a British royal name for  Prince Andrew  (  b. 1960 ), the Duke of York."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Andrew Luttrell Jr was born in 1364, in Irnham, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Andrew Luttrell, was 51 and his mother, Hawise le Despenser, was 20. He married Joan Taillebois about 1390, in Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 31 December 1397, in his hometown, at the age of 33, and was buried in Irnham, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1364–31 DEC 1397":"1364–31. detsember 1397","1364–1397":"1364–1397","1365–1397":"1365–1397","1369–1381":"1369–1381","1383–1418":"1383–1418","1393–1422":"1393–1422","1313–1399":"1313–1399","1344–1414":"1344–1414","about 1393":"umbes 1393","about 1390":"umbes 1390","after 1381":"pärast 1381","1383":"1383","1393":"1393","1381":"1381","7 Sep 1363":"7. september 1363","1414":"1414","1369":"1369","1313":"1313","1422":"1422","1344":"1344","1399":"1399","1365":"1365","1364":"1364","1397":"1397","31 DEC 1397":"31. detsember 1397","BEF    1397":"enne 1397","27 October 1383":"27. oktoober 1383","1418":"1418","Irnham, South Kesteven District, Lincolnshire, England":"Irnham, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Irnham, Lincolnshire, England":"Irnham, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1364–31 DEC 1397":"1364–31. joulukuuta 1397","1364–1397":"1364–1397","1365–1397":"1365–1397","1369–1381":"1369–1381","1383–1418":"1383–1418","1393–1422":"1393–1422","1313–1399":"1313–1399","1344–1414":"1344–1414","about 1393":"noin 1393","about 1390":"noin 1390","after 1381":"1381 jälkeen","1383":"1383","1393":"1393","1381":"1381","7 Sep 1363":"7. syyskuuta 1363","1414":"1414","1369":